{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idb4d8a1be-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s247d–9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"247d–9"},"text":"§ 247d–9.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Dental education for parents of newborns","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary shall develop and implement, through entities that fund or provide perinatal care services to targeted low-income children under a State child health plan under title XXI of the Social Security Act [","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1397aa"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 1397aa","children":[],"tail":" et seq.], a program to deliver oral health educational materials that inform new parents about risks for, and prevention of, early childhood caries and the need for a dental visit within their newborn’s first year of life."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idb4d8a1bf-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/3/tV/s501/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–3, title V, § 501(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-02-04"},"text":"Feb. 4, 2009","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/123/87"},"text":"123 Stat. 87","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idb4d8a1c0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idb4d8a1c1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idb4d8a1c2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Social Security Act, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1935-08-14/ch531"},"text":"act Aug. 14, 1935, ch. 531","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/49/620"},"text":"49 Stat. 620","children":[],"tail":". Title XXI of the Act is classified generally to subchapter XXI (§ 1397aa et seq.) of chapter 7 of this title. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1305"},"text":"section 1305 of this title","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idb4d8a1c3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Children’s Health Insurance Program Reauthorization Act of 2009, and not as part of the Public Health Service Act which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idb4d8a1c4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDate","id":"idb4d8a1c5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section effective ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2009-04-01"},"text":"Apr. 1, 2009","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to child health assistance and medical assistance provided on or after that date, with certain exceptions, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/3/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 111–3","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1396"},"text":"section 1396 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"definitions","id":"idb4d8a1c6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Definition of “Secretary”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“Secretary” means the Secretary of Health and Human Services, see ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/3/s1/c/3"},"text":"section 1(c)(3) of Pub. L. 111–3","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s1396"},"text":"section 1396 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
